.TH "GIT\-HACK" "1" "July 2026" "" ""
.
.SH "NAME"
\fBgit\-hack\fR \- AI\-augmented git workflow helper
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBgit hack\fR [\fIidea\-text\fR]
.
.br
\fBgit hack idea\fR [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR] [\fIidea\-text\fR]
.
.br
\fBgit hack issue\fR [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR] \fInumber\fR
.
.br
\fBgit hack checkpoint\fR [\-a] [\-A] [\-p] [\-n] [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR] [\fIhint\fR]
.
.br
\fBgit hack propose\fR [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR] [\fIhint\fR]
.
.br
\fBgit hack pick\fR [\fIsha\fR] [\fIbranch\fR]
.
.br
\fBgit hack pick\fR \-\-continue
.
.br
\fBgit hack init\fR [\-\-global]
.
.br
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBgit\-hack\fR augments git workflows with AI assistance\. It uses the \fBllm\fR CLI to generate branch names, commit messages, and pull request descriptions, and \fBgit\-town\fR for branch lifecycle management\. Typical flow: create a branch with \fBidea\fR or \fBissue\fR, make changes, checkpoint with \fBcheckpoint\fR, open a PR with \fBpropose\fR, and clean up with \fBgit town sync\fR once it merges\.
.
.P
When invoked without a subcommand, \fBgit hack\fR runs in interactive \fBidea\fR mode\. When invoked with an unrecognised first argument, that argument is treated as an idea description\.
.
.SH "SUBCOMMANDS"
.
.SS "idea (default)"
.
.nf

git hack [idea\-text]
git hack idea [\-y] [\-m model] [idea\-text]
.
.fi
.
.P
Generate a branch name from a free\-text description using \fBllm\fR, then create the branch via \fBgit town hack\fR\. Prompts interactively if \fIidea\-text\fR is omitted\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Accept the AI\-generated branch name without prompting\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.SS "issue"
.
.nf

git hack issue [\-y] [\-m model] <number>
.
.fi
.
.P
Fetch the title and body of a GitHub issue via \fBgh\fR, generate a branch name with \fBllm\fR, and create the branch via \fBgit town hack\fR\. Requires \fBgh\fR to be installed and authenticated (\fBgh auth login\fR)\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Accept the AI\-generated branch name without prompting\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.SS "checkpoint"
.
.nf

git hack checkpoint [\-a] [\-A] [\-p] [\-n] [\-y] [\-m model] [hint]
.
.fi
.
.P
Generate a commit message for staged changes using \fBllm\fR and commit\. If nothing is staged, prompts for \fBp\fR (\fBgit add \-p\fR, interactive patch), \fBa\fR (\fBgit add \-A\fR, all changes), or \fBn\fR (skip)\.
.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-all\fR
Stage all changes (\fBgit add \-A\fR, including untracked files) before generating the message\.
.
.TP
\fB\-A\fR, \fB\-\-amend\fR
Amend the previous commit instead of creating a new one\. Implies \fB\-\-force\-with\-lease\fR when pushing\.
.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-push\fR
Push to origin after committing\.
.
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-no\-verify\fR
Skip pre\-commit and commit\-msg hooks\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Commit with the AI message without prompting\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.TP
\fB<hint>\fR
Optional free\-text guidance passed to the AI to focus the generated commit message on a specific aspect of the diff\.
.
.SS "propose"
.
.nf

git hack propose [\-y] [\-m model] [hint]
.
.fi
.
.P
Generate a PR title and body using \fBllm\fR, then hand them to \fBgit town propose\fR\. git\-town syncs the current branch and opens your forge\'s proposal page prefilled with the generated title and body for you to finalize\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Skip the confirmation of the generated title/body\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.TP
\fB<hint>\fR
Optional free\-text guidance passed to the AI to focus the generated PR title and body on a specific aspect of the changes (e\.g\. "compatibility update for Minecraft 26\.1")\.
.
.SS "pick"
.
.nf

git hack pick [sha] [branch]
git hack pick \-\-continue
.
.fi
.
.P
Cherry\-pick a commit onto the target branch\. When called without arguments, presents an interactive list of recent commits from the default base branch (uses \fBfzf\fR if available)\. After a successful pick, offers to push\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-continue\fR
Resume a cherry\-pick that was paused due to conflicts\. Verifies that all conflicts are resolved and all files are staged before continuing\.
.
.SS "init"
.
.nf

git hack init [\-\-global]
.
.fi
.
.P
Interactive two\-page setup\. Nothing is written without selection\. Targets the current repo by default (\fB\.git/config\fR, \fB\.git/hack/\fR); \fB\-\-global\fR targets \fB~/\.gitconfig\fR and \fB~/\.config/git\-hack/\fR\.
.
.P
Page 1 offers git alias shortcuts:
.
.P
Page 2 offers the prompt\-override files to scaffold (see the prompt keys under CONFIGURATION)\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-global\fR
Write aliases to \fB~/\.gitconfig\fR and prompts to \fB~/\.config/git\-hack/\fR instead of the current repo\.
.
.SH "DEPENDENCIES"
Required:
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBgit\fR — version control
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBllm\fR — AI model CLI (see \fIhttps://llm\.datasette\.io\fR)
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBgit\-town\fR — branch lifecycle management (see \fIhttps://www\.git\-town\.com\fR)
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
Optional:
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBfzf\fR — interactive fuzzy selection for \fBpick\fR and \fBidea\fR
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBgh\fR — GitHub CLI, required for \fBissue\fR subcommand
.
.IP "" 0
.
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
Run once per repository to configure git\-town branch tracking:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

git town config setup
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
Select the \fBllm\fR model to use:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

llm models                          # list available models
llm \-m claude\-3\-5\-sonnet\-latest … # use a specific model
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
The \fB\-m\fR / \fB\-\-model\fR flag on any subcommand overrides the model for a single invocation\.
.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
git(1), git\-town(1), llm(1), gh(1), fzf(1)
